# Component Design Patterns

Reference for designing specific UI components with intentionality. These patterns assume you've already set up CSS variables per the main SKILL.md.

## Buttons

### Hierarchy
Every screen needs at most ONE primary button. Everything else is secondary or ghost.

- **Primary:** Filled with `--color-primary`. White text. Used for the main CTA only.
- **Secondary:** Border or subtle background (`--color-bg-muted`). Used for alternative actions.
- **Ghost:** No background, no border. Text-only with hover state. Used for cancel, back, tertiary actions.
- **Danger:** Red fill or red outline. Only for destructive actions. Always require confirmation for irreversible actions.

### Sizing
- **sm:** `height: 32px`, `padding: 6px 12px`, `font-size: 13px` — inline actions, table rows
- **md:** `height: 40px`, `padding: 10px 20px`, `font-size: 14px` — standard forms
- **lg:** `height: 48px`, `padding: 14px 28px`, `font-size: 16px` — hero CTAs, primary page actions

### States
```
default  → hover (background darken 8-10%) → active (darken 15%) → disabled (40% opacity)
                                                                   → loading (spinner + "Saving...")
```

Loading state: replace the label with a spinner + action verb ("Saving...", "Sending..."). Don't just show a spinner — users need to know what's happening. Keep button width fixed during loading to prevent layout shift.

### Spacing
Icon-to-label gap: `8px`. If the button has only an icon, make it square (40x40 for md).
Buttons in a group: `12px` gap. Primary button on the right (for LTR layouts).

## Form Inputs

### Anatomy
```
Label (14px, font-weight 500, text-secondary)
  ↕ 6px gap
Input field (40px height, 12px horizontal padding, 16px font, border-radius var(--radius-md))
  ↕ 4px gap  
Helper text or error (13px, text-muted or danger)
  ↕ 20-24px gap
Next field group
```

### States
- **Default:** `1px solid var(--color-border)`, white background
- **Hover:** border darkens slightly
- **Focus:** `2px solid var(--color-primary)`, with a subtle primary-colored box-shadow or ring. NEVER remove the focus indicator.
- **Error:** `2px solid var(--color-danger)`, with error message below in `--color-danger`. Also add a small error icon inside the input or beside the label.
- **Disabled:** `background: var(--color-bg-muted)`, reduced opacity on text, cursor: not-allowed

### Textarea
Same styling as input. Default height: 120px (roughly 5 lines). Let it be resizable vertically. Show character count at bottom-right if there's a limit.

### Select / Dropdown
Match input styling exactly. Custom dropdowns should have: max-height (show ~6 options then scroll), hover highlighting on options, keyboard navigation support, a checkmark on the selected option.

### Validation
- **Required fields:** Small asterisk (*) after the label in `--color-danger`. Or mark optional fields instead if most are required.
- **Inline validation:** Validate format on keystroke (email, phone), validate presence on blur. Show error immediately below the input, not in a toast or alert.
- **Form-level errors:** Summary at the top of the form that links to each errored field. Plus inline errors on each field.

## Cards

### When to Use
Cards group related content into a scannable unit. Use them for: dashboard metrics, content previews, list items with detail, settings groups.

### Anatomy
```
Card container (bg-white or bg-subtle, rounded-lg, shadow-sm OR border, NOT both)
├── Header zone (optional): title + description + actions
│     Title: text-lg, font-semibold
│     Description: text-sm, text-secondary
│     Actions: icon buttons or text links, top-right
├── Content zone: the main content
└── Footer zone (optional): metadata, secondary actions
      Separated by a subtle top border or extra spacing
```

Padding: `24px` all around. Increase to `32px` for spacious layouts. Never less than `16px`.

### Variants
- **Elevated:** `shadow-md`, no border. For primary content floating above the page.
- **Outlined:** `1px border`, no shadow. For grids where elevation would be noisy.
- **Filled:** `bg-subtle`, no border, no shadow. For subtle grouping against a white background.
- **Interactive (clickable):** Add `cursor: pointer`, hover state (shadow increase or border color change), and `transition: var(--transition-fast)`.

Don't mix variants in the same card grid. Pick one and use it consistently.

## Navigation

### Sidebar Navigation
- Width: 240–280px. Collapsible to 64px (icon-only) on desktop. Hidden on mobile (hamburger or bottom tabs).
- Items: `40px` height, `12px 16px` padding. Full-width highlight on active item using `--color-primary-subtle` background + `--color-primary` text.
- Sections: Group with small uppercase labels (`11px`, `text-muted`, `letter-spacing: 0.05em`), with `24px` gap between groups.
- Icons: `20px`, consistent stroke weight. Use a single icon library (Lucide, Heroicons, Phosphor). Never mix icon families.

### Top Navigation
- Height: `56–64px`.
- Logo left, primary nav center or left-aligned, user menu / actions right.
- Active state: bottom border or filled background, using primary color.
- Mobile: collapse to hamburger at `768px`.

### Breadcrumbs
- `14px`, `text-secondary`. Separator: `/` or `>` in `text-muted`.
- Current page is `text-primary`, not a link.
- Max 3–4 levels. If deeper, truncate middle items with `...`.

### Tabs
- Use for switching views within the same page (not for navigation between pages).
- Bottom border active indicator: `2px solid primary`.
- Text: `14px`, `font-medium`. Inactive: `text-secondary`. Active: `text-primary`.
- Spacing between tabs: `32px` or `24px`.
- Don't use more than 6 tabs. Beyond that, use a dropdown or secondary navigation.

## Tables

### Design Rules
- **Text alignment:** Left for text, right for numbers, center for status badges and icons only.
- **Header row:** `text-xs` or `text-sm`, `font-medium`, `text-secondary`, `uppercase` or normal case (pick one), `letter-spacing: 0.03em` if uppercase.
- **Cell padding:** `12px 16px` minimum. More vertical padding = more scannable.
- **Row separation:** Use bottom borders (`--color-border-subtle`) OR alternating background colors, never both.
- **Hover:** Subtle background change on row hover if the row is clickable.
- **Sticky header:** Always sticky if the table scrolls. Add a subtle shadow when scrolled.

### Responsive Behavior
Below `768px`, tables should transform into card lists. Each row becomes a card with key-value pairs stacked vertically. Don't try to horizontally scroll a data table on mobile — it's a terrible experience.

### Empty State
Don't show table headers with an empty body. Show a full empty state component with an illustration and CTA.

## Modals / Dialogs

### Sizing
- **sm:** `max-width: 400px` — confirmations, simple forms
- **md:** `max-width: 560px` — standard forms, detail views
- **lg:** `max-width: 720px` — complex content, multi-step flows
- **full:** `max-width: 960px` — should be rare; consider a full page instead

### Anatomy
```
Overlay (black, 40-60% opacity)
└── Modal container (rounded-lg, shadow-lg, white bg)
    ├── Header: Title (text-lg, font-semibold) + Close button (top-right)
    ├── Body: Content with appropriate padding (24-32px)
    └── Footer: Action buttons, right-aligned. Secondary left, Primary right.
         Separated from body by top border or 24px+ gap.
```

### Behavior
- Trap focus inside the modal. ESC to close. Click overlay to close (unless the form has unsaved changes).
- Entrance animation: fade overlay + slide/scale modal (200ms).
- Don't stack modals. If a modal needs to open another modal, reconsider your UX — you probably need a multi-step flow or a slide-over panel instead.

## Toasts / Notifications

- Position: top-right or bottom-right. Consistent throughout the app.
- Max width: `400px`. Auto-dismiss after 4–6 seconds for success, persist for errors.
- Include a dismiss button (×) always.
- Types: success (green left border or icon), error (red), warning (amber), info (blue).
- Don't stack more than 3. If there are more, batch them.
- Animation: slide in from the edge, fade out on dismiss.

## Status Badges / Tags

- Height: `24px` for inline, `28px` for standalone.
- Padding: `4px 10px`. Border-radius: `--radius-full` for pills, `--radius-sm` for rectangular.
- Font: `12px` or `13px`, `font-medium`.
- Color: tinted background + darker text of the same hue. Example: `bg-green-50 text-green-700`, not `bg-green-500 text-white` (too heavy for most contexts).
- Dot indicator: an 8px circle before the label adds clarity. Example: `● Active`, `● Pending`.

## Tooltips

- Appear on hover after `300ms` delay (not instantly — it's annoying).
- Max width: `240px`. Font: `13px`.
- Background: dark (`--color-text` or near-black) with white text, OR white with shadow and dark text.
- Arrow/caret pointing to the trigger element.
- Position: prefer top, fall back to bottom if near viewport edge.
- Keep text concise — one or two sentences max. If you need more, use a popover or help panel.